result.execSummary:
The defendant Philip M Coss was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Entry into/onto Bldg/Constuct.Site/Room, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.15(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 11:47 am [Clerk SH] 
[Reserve Judge Neal Nettesheim presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Philip M Coss in court with Attorney Elizabeth F Svehlek. DA Susan Victoria Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Service of the Information Admitted; Reading Waived
DA Happ submits victim impact statement

On Motion of the State, the Court AMENDS Count #1 to Entry into a Locked Building, contrary to 943.15(1), a Class A Misdemeanor
On Motion fo the State, the Court AMENDS Count #3, to Bailjumping, contrary to 946.49(1)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #1, #2 & #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.

On Counts #1, #2 & #3, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, each count, concurrent, with conditions:
--serve 60 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-release privileges (On Ct#1); to commence at the discretion of the supervising Agent, following current treatment
--AODA Assessment & Follow Through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--Cooperate with and submit to any other type of assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--Continue educational efforts
--Maintain absolute sobriety
--No presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores
--To pay costs of $729
--To pay $600 DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
--To pay restitution of $600, payable to Kevin Klaty
--To pay 10% restitution processing fee
--Random drug screens at discretion of agent
Jail sentence may transfer to Waukesha or Milwaukee County as long as electronic monitoring is not utilized

Days credit for time already served: 3 days
